gime (Walter Gropius, Paul Hindemith, Gottfried Benn, Ernst Barlach, Emil Nolde) as well as others whose desire for official acceptance was realized (Richard Strauss, Gustaf Gründgens, Leni Riefenstahl, Arno Breker, Albert Speer). Collectively these ten figures illuminate the complex cultural history of Nazi Germany, while individually they provide haunting portraits of people facing excruciating choices and grave moral questions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210613423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300210613.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO